Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The 68 dashboard pages were registered ad-hoc in App.tsx, with three routes
(tradingview-chart, bloomberg-terminal, news-monitor) accidentally registered
twice. There was also no client-side authorization at all — any browser tab
could hit /execution-control or /risk-command-v2 and submit destructive
mutations. Fixed both:

1. src/pages/page-manifest.ts — every page is now a single entry containing
   path, scope, label, lazy loader, and minRole. App.tsx maps over the
   manifest to build <Route> elements; duplicate paths are now impossible by
   construction (the manifest module asserts uniqueness at load time and
   throws on violation).

2. src/auth/role-context.tsx + route-guard.tsx — RoleProvider exposes
   { role, setRole, can }. RouteGuard renders an access-denied panel with a
   one-click elevation button when the page's minRole isn't satisfied. Server
   remains the source of truth (Phase 2's require503IfNoBroker still
   fail-closes broker endpoints in production); this client gate adds
   intent-confirmation and routing-level affordances.

3. src/auth/role-switcher.tsx — small viewer/operator toggle in the Shell
   footer for unauthenticated dev rollouts. Will be replaced by SSO claims in
   a future auth integration.

4. App.tsx shrinks from 282 lines to 154 (removed 67 import lines + 67 route
   declarations + 3 duplicate routes). Same routing surface, half the lines,
   no possible drift.

5. PAGES.md — concrete migration backlog for the fetch → React Query
   conversion. Audit categorizes all 68 pages: 4 rq-only (gold standard),
   31 mixed, 20 raw-fetch, 13 static. Phase 5/6 will work this backlog.

Operator-gated paths (12): /command-center, /execution, /execution-control,
/exec-reliability, /risk, /risk-command-v2, /advanced-risk, /capital-gating,
/paper-trading-program, /ops-security, /model-governance, /settings.

Verification: tsc --build exits 0 across the workspace (all 68 manifest
imports resolved, RoleProvider + RouteGuard type-check, App.tsx wiring
type-checks).

